docs.abstract: Lower supplies of the gas mean that beer loses its fizz and some meat can’t be packaged. That could affect the supply of some staples of British summers.
docs.snippet: Lower supplies of the gas mean that beer loses its fizz and some meat can’t be packaged. That could affect the supply of some staples of British summers.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Beer, barbecues and crumpets, three staples of life in Britain as it enjoys an unusually warm summer, may soon experience shortages as the country faces an unexpected shortfall — of carbon dioxide.

headline.main: U.K. Fears for Its Beer and Crumpets. Blame a Carbon Dioxide Shortage.
headline.print_headline: Gas Shortage Threatens to Flatten British Staples

docs.abstract: As the European Union faces a potential trade war with the United States, its resolve is likely to be tested by differing interests within the bloc.
docs.snippet: As the European Union faces a potential trade war with the United States, its resolve is likely to be tested by differing interests within the bloc.
docs.lead_paragraph: ROME — For Europe, the first move was easy. Officials swiftly announced plans to strike back with retaliatory measures against President Trump’s tariffs on steel and aluminum while vowing a legal challenge.

headline.main: For Europe, an Unpleasant Question: Confront Trump or Avoid a Costly Trade War
headline.print_headline: U.S. Tariffs Sow Further Discord In Divided E.U.

docs.abstract: Turkey’s descent into authoritarianism and crisis has destroyed whatever hopes remained that the country’s president might serve as a force for moderation.
docs.snippet: Turkey’s descent into authoritarianism and crisis has destroyed whatever hopes remained that the country’s president might serve as a force for moderation.
docs.lead_paragraph: In Western capitals a decade ago, Turkey’s now-paramount leader, Recep Tayyip Erdogan, held promise as a potential beacon of democracy for a region rife with religious conflict.

headline.main: The West Hoped for Democracy in Turkey. Erdogan Had Other Ideas.
headline.print_headline: The West Saw a Democracy;  Turkey Embraced an Autocrat

docs.abstract: Like his father before him, Mr. Rice was a Rupert Murdoch loyalist. With Disney acquiring 21st Century Fox, he is about to start a new chapter.
docs.snippet: Like his father before him, Mr. Rice was a Rupert Murdoch loyalist. With Disney acquiring 21st Century Fox, he is about to start a new chapter.
docs.lead_paragraph: Hollywood executives are not so different from the stars they employ. They want to be seen in the right booths at the right restaurants. They work the room at the after-parties on awards nights. And they would rather die than drop a spot on The Hollywood Reporter’s annual power list.

headline.main: Peter Rice, Fox’s Un-Hollywood TV Boss, Is Getting More Say Over What You Watch
headline.print_headline: New Chapter at Disney For Fox’s Master of TV

docs.abstract: Google did not notify authorities of the vulnerabilities in Google Plus, which exposed the data of up to 500,000 users.
docs.snippet: Google did not notify authorities of the vulnerabilities in Google Plus, which exposed the data of up to 500,000 users.
docs.lead_paragraph: Google said on Monday that it would shut down Google Plus, the company’s long-struggling answer to Facebook’s giant social network, after it discovered a security vulnerability that exposed the private data of up to 500,000 users.

headline.main: Google Plus Will Be Shut Down After User Information Was Exposed
headline.print_headline: Google Plus Shutting Down After User Data Was Exposed

docs.abstract: A proposed ordinance would ban employee cafeterias in new construction, encouraging tech workers to leave the office to buy their meals.
docs.snippet: A proposed ordinance would ban employee cafeterias in new construction, encouraging tech workers to leave the office to buy their meals.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The corporate campuses of the Bay Area’s technology companies have become independent fiefs with dry cleaning, gyms, doctors, shuttle buses and bountiful free meals, made by the best chefs poached from the region’s famous restaurants. Now, local officials are knocking at the gates.

headline.main: San Francisco Officials to Tech Workers: Buy Your Lunch
headline.print_headline: San Francisco Measure Targets A Tech Staple: The Free Lunch
